12) Define Transverse Wave and State its Characteristics

Definition: A wave where particle displacement is perpendicular to the wave’s direction.
Characteristics:
Contains crests (high points) and troughs (low points).
Has measurable wavelength and frequency.
Amplitude measures the maximum particle displacement.
13) Define Longitudinal Wave and State its Characteristics

Definition: A wave where particles oscillate parallel to the wave’s direction.
Characteristics:
Compressions (high pressure) and rarefactions (low pressure).
Wavelength and frequency define properties.
Sound waves are common longitudinal waves.
14) Common Properties of Waves

Reflection: Bouncing off surfaces.
Refraction: Bending when moving through different media.
Diffraction: Spreading around obstacles.
Interference: Waves superimpose to form new wave patterns.
Polarization: Restricting wave vibrations to a specific direction (for transverse waves).
15) Doppler Effect

Definition: The change in frequency or wavelength due to relative motion between source and observer.
Application: Used in radar, medical imaging, and astronomy to measure speed or distance changes.
